Base:Descriptions.Base:Description: Dock Street

A wooden boardwalk known as Dock Street. Morning has broken and the first rays of sunshine can be seen shimmering down. The sun has risen and the hustle and bustle of the city is audible. The midday sun is high in the sky and waves of heat can be seen shimmering off the wooden planking. The bright blue skies of the afternoon bathe every corner of the boardwalk in sunlight. The sun has set and the boardwalk is shadowed in the failing light. Evening has fallen and the boardwalk is dimmed. There is a slight chill in the air. Midnight has enveloped the silent boardwalk. A slight lightening of the sky bathes the boardwalk in an eerie light as dawn approaches. A long stretch of wooden boardwalk known as Dock Street, which continues on to the east and the west. A long, L-shaped pier stands to the southeast and an opening to the north leads to a cobbled alley. To the northwest, a solid oak door stands under a quaint hanging wooden sign that reads "Mama and Papa's Fish Shack" in chunky block text. A small window allows a view into the building.
